===message:You have some great points in your discussion.  In my thoughts the 1950's were the begining of a transition for working woman.  If we look back in history a woman's role was that of taking care of the home and children.  While men handled everything outside of the home.  You are correct there are alot more opportunities for woman in modern society.  I think this has to do with the change in thinking that has occured over the years.  It was normal for a woman to be a housewife back them and generally more accepted.  In today's world woman who choose to stay at home a far ournumbered by the working wives.  I think the divorce rate is impacted slightly by the "independent woman" but there are far to many other factors involved.  Now woman are more likely to leave their spouse because they feel and have every right to, that they can do things on there own.  
