===subject:Chapter 9 Reply
===from:Carla Foster
===date:Sun Apr 13 16:50:59 2003
===message:James,

I do not agree that the increase in the divorce rate is contributed to the independence of the "modern women."  I believe the rise in the divorce rate is contributed to other factors such as lack of communication, financial pressures, domestic violence, alcoholism, and work stress leaving less time for family.  I also believe most men today appreciate the independence of the "modern women."  Such a woman becomes a helpmate, not a dependant, within the marriage.
=========yorg=========
